# **Smart ATS Resume Analyser**

An AI-powered, full-stack web application built with Java Spring Boot and Spring Security. This tool provides a "production-level" analysis of a user's resume against a job description, combining code-based compliance checks with advanced ML-driven feedback from the Google Gemini API.

This project was developed to move beyond simple keyword matching and provide job seekers with actionable, expert-level insights to help them pass modern Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS).

![][image1]

## **‚ú® Core Features**

* **Secure User Authentication:** Full user registration, login, and session management using Spring Security and a MySQL database. Passwords are all hashed using BCrypt.  
* **AI-Powered Analysis:** Leverages the Google Gemini API to provide a deep, qualitative review of the resume.  
* **Dynamic Visual Scorecard:** Parses the AI's report to build a visual, chart-based scorecard for categories like **Brevity**, **Impact**, **Technical Skills**, and **Style**.  
* **Code-Based Compliance Engine:**  
  * Parses .pdf and .docx files using **Apache Tika**.  
  * Detects **images and tables** in .docx files using **Apache POI**.  
  * Checks for file type and inconsistent date formats using **Regex**.  
* **Multi-Page Layout:** A unified, professional frontend built with Thymeleaf Layout Dialect, including a persistent navigation bar.  
* **Analysis History:** Logged-in users can view all their past analysis reports on a dedicated /history page.  
* **Modern UI/UX:**  
  * Beautiful, responsive "glassmorphism" UI that works on desktop and mobile.  
  * **Light/Dark Mode** toggle with user preference saved in localStorage.  
  * Animated loading indicators to provide user feedback during AI analysis.

## **üõ†Ô∏è Technology Stack**

A breakdown of the key technologies and libraries used in this project.

| Category | Technology | Purpose |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Backend** | Java 17 | Core programming language. |
|  | Spring Boot 3 | Framework for the entire application (Web, Security, JPA). |
|  | Spring Security 6 | Handles user authentication, authorization, and CSRF protection. |
|  | RestTemplate | Makes HTTP calls to the Google Gemini API. |
| **Frontend** | Thymeleaf | Server-side Java template engine for dynamic HTML. |
|  | Bootstrap 5 | CSS framework for the responsive, modern UI. |
|  | JavaScript | Powers the light/dark mode, loading bar, and visual scorecard. |
|  | CommonMark | Java library to parse the AI's Markdown response into HTML. |
| **Database** | MySQL | Relational database to store user and analysis report data. |
|  | Spring Data JPA | Handles all database interactions, mapping Java objects to tables. |
| **File Parsing** | Apache Tika | Extracts plain text from .pdf and .docx files. |
|  | Apache POI | Analyzes the *structure* of .docx files to find images/tables. |
| **Build** | Apache Maven | Manages all project dependencies and builds the application. |

## **üöÄ Getting Started**

Follow these instructions to get a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing.

### **Prerequisites**

You will need the following tools installed on your system:

* **Java 17 (or newer):** The project is built on Java 17\.  
* **Apache Maven:** To manage dependencies and run the project.  
* **MySQL Server:** A running MySQL instance (like MySQL Community Server or XAMPP).

### **1\. Clone the Repository**

git clone 

https://github.com//anant-925//ats-resume-analyser

cd ats-resume-analyser

### **2\. Set Up Your Database**

You must create a MySQL database for the application to use.

1. Log in to your MySQL client (e.g., MySQL Workbench or the mysql command line).  
2. Run the following command to create the database:  
   CREATE DATABASE ats\_analyser\_db;

   *Spring Boot (via Hibernate) will automatically create all the necessary tables (users, analysis\_reports) when it first starts.*

### **3\. Configure Your Environment**

This is the most important step. You must provide your database password and your secret API key.

1. Navigate to src/main/resources/.  
2. Create a new file named application.properties.  
3. **Copy and paste** the code block below into your new application.properties file.  
4. **Change** your\_mysql\_password to your actual MySQL password.  
5. **Change** your\_google\_api\_key with your key from Google.

\# \--- DATABASE CONFIGURATION \---  
\# The URL to your new database  
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/ats\_analyser\_db  
\# Your MySQL username (usually 'root')  
spring.datasource.username=root  
\# \!\!\! REPLACE THIS WITH YOUR MYSQL PASSWORD \!\!\!  
spring.datasource.password=your\_mysql\_password

\# \--- JPA CONFIGURATION \---  
\# This tells JPA (Hibernate) to automatically create/update your database tables  
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update  
\# This shows the SQL commands in your log, which is helpful for debugging  
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

\# \--- GEMINI API KEY \---  
\# \!\!\! REPLACE THIS WITH YOUR GOOGLE AI API KEY \!\!\!  
gemini.api.key=your\_google\_api\_key

#### **How to get your Google API Key:**

1. Go to [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey) and generate a new API key.  
2. Go to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/), select the same project, and ensure the **"Vertex AI API"** (or "Generative Language API") is **ENABLED**. If you skip this, you will get 404 errors.

### **4\. Build and Run the Application**

You can now run the application using the Maven wrapper.

\# Clean the project and run all tests (recommended first time)  
./mvnw clean install

\# Run the application  
./mvnw spring-boot:run

Your server will start on http://localhost:8080.

### **5\. Using the App**

* Go to **http://localhost:8080/register** to create a new user.  
* Go to **http://localhost:8080/login** to log in.  
* Go to **http://localhost:8080/** to start analyzing your resumes\!  
* Go to **http://localhost:8080/history** to see your saved reports.
